race.comment: Open race to close out the card. IRON POWER (3) resumes here but has a very solid fresh record not missing a drum in four first-up attempts. Drawn to get a cosy run in transit from gate three and should be right there at the business end. SHIPPING LANE (2) broke the maiden status three back and has been thereabouts in both runs since. Capable of a strong showing. The well-related BILLY BOOM (7) (half to G3 winner Metalart) strips fitter third-up from the spell and is capable of featuring on best figures. REVITUP CHARLIE (15) doesn't win out of turn but is usually up in the firing line and can give backers a sight. ARTOPIA (10) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be underestimated.
